QuestData.Title: Raptor Hunting
QuestData.Description: So you think your hunting skills are in tip-top shape? I can put them to the test in a jiffy. Head out into that jungle and kill ten Stranglethorn raptors. We'll see just how much of a big game hunter you are.$b$bAnd no, I won't tell you where you can find them! Locating the beasts is half the challenge.$b$bOkay, go west.
QuestData.CompletionText: I never met a hunter who got any kills by standing around the campfire - well, except for my father. Were you planning on killing those Stranglethorn Raptors or were you hoping they would die of old age?
QuestData.RewardText: Stranglethorn raptors were not a problem for a wily $c like you.
